            </persName>
            <birth when="1225"/>
            <death when="1274"/>
            <note>Italian Dominican friar and priest, an influential philosopher and theologian, and a jurist in the tradition of scholasticism from the county of Aquino in the Kingdom of Sicily. Thomas was a prominent proponent of natural theology and the father of a school of thought known as Thomism.</note>
         </person>
